### Example 6: Paint Mixing on a Bar Chart

<!-- BUILD: Mix paint in a ratio (3 parts red, 2 parts yellow). Draw a simple bar showing the proportion visually. Use plot/bar with two categories. -->

```scheme
(define red-parts 3)
(define yellow-parts 2)

(define data (list (list \"Red\" red-parts)
                   (list \"Yellow\" yellow-parts)))

(define p (plot/bar data))

(print \"Paint mix ratio: \" red-parts \" parts red, \" yellow-parts \" parts yellow\")
(print (plot/render-svg p 400 300))
```

[VISUAL: Bar chart with two bars—Red (height 3), Yellow (height 2)—showing the 3:2 ratio visually]

