### Example 7: Unit Rate on a Number Line (Speed)

<!-- BUILD: Mark a number line from 0 to 50 (miles per hour). Plot a point at the computed unit rate. Use plot/scatter with a single point. -->

```scheme
(define miles 90)
(define hours 2)
(define rate (exact/->float (exact/rat miles hours)))

(define p (plot/scatter (list (list rate 0))
                        #:x-min 0
                        #:x-max 50
                        #:y-min -1
                        #:y-max 1
                        #:x-label \"miles per hour\"
                        #:y-label \"\"))

(print \"Unit rate: \" rate \" mph\")
(print (plot/render-svg p 400 100))
```

[VISUAL: Number line (x-axis 0 to 50), single point at x=45.0 (the unit rate), y=0]

