### Example 18: Scale Model (Map Scale)

<!-- BUILD: A map scale is 1 cm = 50 km. If two cities are 3.5 cm apart on the map, how far apart are they in reality? Solve the proportion. -->

```scheme
(define map-scale-cm 1)
(define map-scale-km 50)
(define map-distance-cm 3.5)

(define real-distance-km (* (exact/->float (exact/rat map-distance-cm map-scale-cm)) map-scale-km))

(print \"Map scale: \" map-scale-cm \" cm = \" map-scale-km \" km\")
(print \"Map distance: \" map-distance-cm \" cm\")
(print \"Real distance: \" real-distance-km \" km\")
```

[VISUAL: Printed output showing 3.5 cm on map = 175.0 km in reality]

---

### Example 19: Recipe Scaling (Fractional Scale Factor)

<!-- BUILD: A recipe calls for 2.5 cups flour for 12 cookies. How much flour for 30 cookies? Set up and solve the proportion. -->

```scheme
(define flour-original 2.5)
(define cookies-original 12)
(define cookies-new 30)

(define flour-new (* (exact/->float (exact/rat cookies-new cookies-original)) flour-original))

(print \"Original: \" flour-original \" cups flour for \" cookies-original \" cookies\")
(print \"New: \" cookies-new \" cookies\")
(print \"Flour needed: \" flour-new \" cups\")
```

[VISUAL: Printed output showing 30 cookies require 6.25 cups flour]

