### Example 20: Similar Triangles (Proportional Side Lengths)

<!-- BUILD: Two similar triangles. Triangle A has sides 3, 4, 5. Triangle B has the first side 6 (scale factor 2). Compute the other sides of B using proportion. -->

```scheme
(define a1 3)
(define a2 4)
(define a3 5)

(define b1 6)
(define scale (exact/rat b1 a1))

(define b2 (exact/->float (exact/* scale (exact/rat a2 1))))
(define b3 (exact/->float (exact/* scale (exact/rat a3 1))))

(print \"Triangle A: \" a1 \", \" a2 \", \" a3)
(print \"Triangle B (similar, first side \" b1 \"): \" b1 \", \" b2 \", \" b3)
(print \"Scale factor: \" (exact/->string scale))
```

[VISUAL: Printed output showing Triangle B sides are 6, 8.0, 10.0 (double Triangle A)]

