### Example 21: Constant of Proportionality from Data

<!-- BUILD: Given (x, y) pairs where y is proportional to x, compute k = y/x for each pair (should be constant), then average them (as a check). Print k. -->

```scheme
(define data (list (list 2 7)
                   (list 3 10.5)
                   (list 4 14)
                   (list 5 17.5)))

(define ks (map (lambda (pair)
                  (exact/->float (exact/rat (cadr pair) (car pair))))
                data))

(print \"x\\ty\\tk=y/x\")
(map (lambda (pair k)
       (print (car pair) \"\\t\" (cadr pair) \"\\t\" k))
     data ks)

(define k-avg (/ (apply + ks) (length ks)))
(print \"Average k: \" k-avg \" (constant of proportionality)\")
```

[VISUAL: Printed table showing k = 3.5 for every pair, confirming y = 3.5x]

