### Example 22: Percent as a Proportion (Part Over Whole)

<!-- BUILD: 18 out of 25 students passed. What percent? Set up 18/25 = x/100, solve for x. -->

```scheme
(define passed 18)
(define total 25)

(define percent (exact/->float (exact/* (exact/rat passed total) (exact/rat 100 1))))

(print passed \" out of \" total \" students passed.\")
(print \"Percent: \" percent \"%\")
```

[VISUAL: Printed output showing 72.0%]

Percent literally means \"per hundred\"—a proportion where the denominator is 100.

