### Example 24: Proportional Scaling on the Canvas (Rectangle)

<!-- BUILD: Draw two rectangles, one 3×2, the other scaled by factor 2.5 (so 7.5×5). Use plot/scatter to mark the corners, or describe the coordinates. -->

```scheme
(define width-original 3)
(define height-original 2)
(define scale-factor 2.5)

(define width-new (* width-original scale-factor))
(define height-new (* height-original scale-factor))

(print \"Original rectangle: \" width-original \" × \" height-original)
(print \"Scaled by \" scale-factor \": \" width-new \" × \" height-new)
(print \"Corners of scaled rectangle: (0,0), (\" width-new \",0), (\" width-new \",\" height-new \"), (0,\" height-new \")\")
```

[VISUAL: Printed coordinates showing the scaled rectangle is 7.5 × 5.0]

