### Example 34: Denseness of Rationals (Average of Two Rationals)

<!-- BUILD: Given two rationals, find their average (midpoint on the number line). This shows that between any two rationals, there's another rational. -->

```scheme
(define a (exact/rat 1 3))
(define b (exact/rat 1 2))

(define midpoint (exact// (exact/+ a b) (exact/rat 2 1)))

(print (exact/->string a) \" and \" (exact/->string b))
(print \"Midpoint: \" (exact/->string midpoint))
(print \"Between any two rationals, there's always another rational.\")
