### Example 46: Probability of Rolling a Sum of 7 (Two Dice)

<!-- BUILD: Count how many of the 36 outcomes sum to 7. Compute probability. -->

```scheme
(define die-1 (list 1 2 3 4 5 6))
(define die-2 (list 1 2 3 4 5 6))

(define outcomes
  (apply append
         (map (lambda (d1)
                (map (lambda (d2) (list d1 d2)) die-2))
              die-1)))

(define sum-7-outcomes (filter (lambda (pair) (= (+ (car pair) (cadr pair)) 7)) outcomes))

(define prob (exact/rat (length sum-7-outcomes) (length outcomes)))

(print \"Outcomes that sum to 7: \" sum-7-outcomes)
(print \"Count: \" (length sum-7-outcomes))
(print \"Probability: \" (exact/->string prob) \" = \" (exact/->float prob))
```

[VISUAL: Printed output showing 6 outcomes sum to 7: (1,6), (2,5), (3,4), (4,3), (5,2), (6,1); P(sum=7) = 6/36 = 1/6]

