### Example 47: Theoretical vs. Experimental Probability (Spinner)

<!-- BUILD: A spinner with 4 equal sections (Red, Blue, Green, Yellow). Theoretical P(Red) = 1/4. Simulate 200 spins, compute experimental P(Red). Print both. -->

```scheme
(define sections (list \"Red\" \"Blue\" \"Green\" \"Yellow\"))
(define n-spins 200)

; Simulate spins
(define (spin i) (list-ref sections (modulo (* i 7919) 4)))

(define spins (map spin (range 1 (+ n-spins 1))))
(define red-count (length (filter (lambda (s) (equal? s \"Red\")) spins)))

(define theoretical-prob (exact/rat 1 4))
(define experimental-prob (exact/->float (exact/rat red-count n-spins)))

(print \"Theoretical P(Red): \" (exact/->string theoretical-prob) \" = \" (exact/->float theoretical-prob))
(print \"Simulated \" n-spins \" spins. Red appeared \" red-count \" times.\")
(print \"Experimental P(Red): \" experimental-prob)
```

[VISUAL: Printed output showing theoretical 0.25, experimental close to 0.25 (e.g. 0.26 or 0.24)]

