### Example 49: Expected Value (Simple Lottery)

<!-- BUILD: A lottery: $1 ticket. Win $10 with probability 1/20, win $0 otherwise. Compute expected value: E = (1/20)*10 + (19/20)*0 = 0.5. Compare to ticket cost. -->

```scheme
(define ticket-cost 1.0)
(define win-amount 10.0)
(define prob-win (exact/rat 1 20))
(define prob-lose (exact/- (exact/rat 1 1) prob-win))

(define expected-value (+ (* (exact/->float prob-win) win-amount)
                          (* (exact/->float prob-lose) 0)))

(print \"Lottery: $\" ticket-cost \" ticket, win $\" win-amount \" with probability \" (exact/->string prob-win))
(print \"Expected value: $\" expected-value)
(print \"You pay $\" ticket-cost \", so expected loss: $\" (- ticket-cost expected-value))
```

[VISUAL: Printed output showing expected value $0.50, so you lose $0.50 per ticket on average]

**Expected value** is the long-run average outcome. If you play this lottery many times, you'll average a $0.50 return per ticket, losing $0.50 each time (because the ticket costs $1).

---

### Example 50: Probability on a Spinner (Unequal Sections)

<!-- BUILD: A spinner divided into three sections: Red (1/2 of the circle), Blue (1/3), Green (1/6). Compute probabilities. Print them. -->

```scheme
(define prob-red (exact/rat 1 2))
(define prob-blue (exact/rat 1 3))
(define prob-green (exact/rat 1 6))

(print \"Spinner sections:\")
(print \"  Red: \" (exact/->string prob-red))
(print \"  Blue: \" (exact/->string prob-blue))
(print \"  Green: \" (exact/->string prob-green))

(define total-prob (exact/+ prob-red (exact/+ prob-blue prob-green)))
(print \"Total probability (should be 1): \" (exact/->string total-prob))
```

[VISUAL: Printed output showing P(Red)=1/2, P(Blue)=1/3, P(Green)=1/6; sum = 1]

Not all outcomes have to be equally likely—probabilities just have to sum to 1.

