### Example 58: Area of a Triangle (Base and Height)

<!-- BUILD: Compute area of a triangle with base 8, height 5, using geom/triangle-area. -->

```scheme
(define base 8)
(define height 5)

(define t (geom/triangle base height 0 0))  ; triangle positioned at origin
(define area (geom/triangle-area t))

(print \"Triangle: base \" base \", height \" height)
(print \"Area: \" area)
```

[VISUAL: Printed output showing area = 20.0]

The formula is A = (1/2) × base × height.

---

### Example 59: Area of a Composite Shape (Rectangle + Semicircle)

<!-- BUILD: A shape made of a rectangle (width 10, height 4) with a semicircle (radius 5) on top. Compute total area. -->

```scheme
(define rect-width 10)
(define rect-height 4)
(define semi-radius 5)

(define rect-area (* rect-width rect-height))
(define semi-area (/ (geom/circle-area semi-radius) 2))

(define total-area (+ rect-area semi-area))

(print \"Composite shape:\")
(print \"  Rectangle: \" rect-width \" × \" rect-height \" = area \" rect-area)
(print \"  Semicircle: radius \" semi-radius \" = area \" semi-area)
(print \"Total area: \" total-area)
```

[VISUAL: Printed output showing rectangle area 40, semicircle area ≈ 39.27, total ≈ 79.27]

---

### Example 60: Plotting a Circle (Parametric)

<!-- BUILD: Plot a circle of radius 3 centered at the origin using plot/parametric. The parametric equations are x = r cos(t), y = r sin(t), t from 0 to 2π. -->
")
